Possess THC (2nd+offense) - No contest plea.  Convicted.  Sentence is withheld.  Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for two (2) years.  Conditions of probation are:
1) Sixty (60) days jail, under the Huber Law, imposed and stayed, to be imposed upon the agent's discretion;
2) Sixty (60) hours community service work;
3) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
4) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
5) Maintain full-time employment/schooling combination;
6) Pay costs of action;
7) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
8) Provide DNA sample.  
